The same applies to C# though, correct? Plus, I was thinking more of the lines of something like:<p><pre><code>    class Foo {
      private int x = 0;

      public void bar() {
        this.x += 1; // Whoops!
      }
    }

    Foo x = new Foo();
    x.bar(); // Mutating call.
</code></pre>
Which Java does not prevent.
